  = section "C1 = PH/TH/KH/TSH/ČH" do
    %p Roots with initial aspirates are largely unproblematic. Since #{template "C1"} is always in a cluster, it will always surface in an unaspirated state. The only difference between this and the regular paradigms is that any short vowel immediately preceding #{template "C1"} will reduce to /ə/. One such root is *čhlās “laugh”, giving the verb #{t "νίττζαλας", "nitčalas"} “laugh”.

