  = section "C3 = PH/TH/KH/TSH/ČH" do
    %p The most irregular aspirate subclass in Scale V is, naturally, the #{template "C3"} aspirates, although this irregularity mostly mirrors that of other scales. The aspiration will only surface when intervocal, short vowels immediately preceding #{template "C3"} will reduce to schwa, and the preterite and imperfect use the special set of aspirated endings. Note, however, the special #{template "C3"} metathesis that takes place in some forms of the past tenses, whereby the usual stems #{template "*nitC1aC2aC3-"} (preterite) and #{template "*nitC1ieC2eC3-"} (imperfect) become #{template "*nitC1aC2C3ə-"} and #{template "*nitC1ieC2C3e-"} The chart below demonstrates the conjugation of the verb #{t "νίτραχατζ", "nitraxəč"} “bathe, wash oneself”, from the root *rxāčh “wash”.
